# CODEOWNERS — reviewers required for security-sensitive paths.
#
# Wire this up in Gitea: Settings → Branches → Protected Branches →
# enable "Require code owner review" on `main` and `dev`.
#
# Any PR touching these paths must be approved by the listed owner
# before it can merge. This is the first line of defense against
# workflow tampering that could exfiltrate CI secrets once release
# automation lands.

# CI/CD workflow files — anyone editing these can change what runs on
# the runner and (once release.yml exists) potentially access signer
# keys.
.gitea/workflows/    @ericdong

# Tauri config — controls CSP, updater endpoint, signing pubkey, and
# global Tauri API exposure. Treat as security-critical.
tauri.conf.json      @ericdong

# Cargo manifest — controls which shannon-code rev is pulled in and
# what features are enabled by default.
Cargo.toml           @ericdong

# Release documentation — describes the signing key rotation flow.
docs/RELEASING.md    @ericdong
